{
  "text": "In parallel to the computation of the outputs of the filter banks, a fast Fourier transform is used for spectral estimation. Based on the power spectrum, a masking curve is calculated. Quantization noise is then allocated in the various subbands according to the masking function [CITATION_1] . This allocation is done on a small block of subband samples. The psychoacoustic model gives, for each subband, a minimum SNR that the subband coding algorithm must reach in order to limit the quantization noise introduced during this compression operation. The quality of the coded-decoded audio frames is adjusted by the quality ratio coefficients (Qr), defined as,",
